{{Infobox concert tour | concert_tour_name = 20th Anniversary Farewell Tour | type = World | image = Farewell Tour Costa Rica Rhapsody.jpg | image_caption = Rhapsody's 20th Anniversary Farewell Tour live in San Jose Costa Rica, Jan 20, 2018. | location= Europe, South America, Asia, North America | artist = [[Rhapsody of Fire|Rhapsody]] | album = | start_date = April 26, 2017 | end_date = March 20, 2018<!--- Do not add (to date) as March 20, 2018 is their final show of the tour. ---> | number_of_legs = 7 | number_of_shows = 73 | last_tour = ''Demons, Dragons & Warriors World Tour'' (2005) | this_tour = '''''20th Anniversary Farewell Tour''''' (2017-2018) | next_tour = – }}
The '''20th Anniversary Farewell Tour''' was a concert tour by former members of [[Rhapsody of Fire|Rhapsody]]. It was announced on November 21, 2016 by ex-Rhapsody members [[Luca Turilli]] (founder and composer), [[Fabio Lione]] (lead singer), [[Patrice Guers]], [[Dominique Leurquin]] and [[Alex Holzwarth]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/rhapsody-announces-20th-anniversary-farewell-tour/|title=RHAPSODY Announces '20th Anniversary Farewell Tour'|date=21 November 2016|publisher=Blabbermouth}}</ref> It celebrated the 20th anniversary of ''[[Legendary Tales]]'' and had a number of their classic hits played at their shows, along with ''[[Symphony of Enchanted Lands]]'' in its entirety.
Fabio has stated that the original band would no longer exist as the other members want to do different music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bravewords.com/news/fabio-lione-talks-rhapsody-reunion-after-this-tour-the-original-band-rhapsody-will-not-exist-anymore|title=FABIO LIONE Talks RHAPSODY Reunion – "After This Tour The ‘Original’ Band RHAPSODY Will Not Exist Anymore"|first=|last=bravewords.com|publisher=|accessdate=5 May 2017}}</ref> Keyboardist [[Alex Staropoli]] did not play on this tour.
