{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=August 2015}} {{primary sources|date=March 2011}} {{Infobox music festival | name =Creamfields Australia | image =David Guetta (7124174409).jpg | caption = [[David Guetta]] performing at Creamfields Australia 2012 | location =[[Australia]] | years_active =2010-2012, 2017-present | founders =[[Onelove]] | dates = | genre = [[Electronic music]], | attendance = | capacity = | website ={{Official website|http://www.creamfieldsaus.com/}} }} '''Creamfields Australia''' is a dance music [[festival]] held in major cities throughout [[Australia]] and is a spinoff of the UK festival [[Creamfields]]. Events company/brand Totem [[Onelove]], who also produce [[Stereosonic]], brought the brand to Australia in 2010 until it was cancelled in 2012.
In 2017, the festival was restarted annually as a single day event<ref>https://www.electronic-festivals.com/event/creamfields-australia</ref> by promoter Dance Nation Australia.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}} Headliners for the 2017 event included [[Deadmau5]], [[Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike]], [[Don Diablo]], Fedde Le Grand, Gareth Emery, [[Oliver Heldens]], [[Showtek]], and Sunnery James & Ryan Marciano.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}
Other Creamfields spinoff festivals have been held throughout the world in cities such as [[Abu Dhabi]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.creamfields.ae/|title=CREAMFIELDS ABU DHABI 2014 - ThinkFlash|publisher=}}</ref> (United Arab Emirates), [[Buenos Aires]] (Argentina), [[Andalucía]] (Spain), [[Punchestown]] (Ireland), [[Punta del Este]] (Uruguay), [[Alcala de Henares]] (Spain), [[Istanbul]] (Turkey), [[Vilnius]] (Lithuania), [[Mexico City]] (Mexico), [[Moscow]] (Russia), [[Prague]] (Czech Republic), [[Lima]] (Peru), [[Santiago]] (Chile), [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Curitiba]], [[Belo Horizonte]] (Brazil),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.creamfields.com.br/2011/index.php|title=Creamfields Brasil|publisher=}}</ref> [[Malta]], [[Wrocław]] (Poland) and [[Lisbon]] (Portugal).
