{{Politics of Grenada}}
'''General elections''' were held in [[Grenada]] on 3 December 1984,<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p307 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> the first after the [[Invasion of Grenada|invasion]] that followed two coups. The result was a victory for the [[New National Party (Grenada)|New National Party]], which won 14 of the 15 seats. Voter turnout was 86.2%.<ref>Nohlen, p310</ref>
