'''Operation Bayonet''' was a multinational law enforcement operation culminating in 2017 targeting the [[AlphaBay]] and [[Hansa (market)|Hansa]] [[darknet market]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/illegal-goods-website-alphabay-shut-following-law-enforcement-action-1499968444|title=Illegal-Goods Website AlphaBay Shut Following Law-Enforcement Action|last=McMillan|first=Robert|last2=Viswanatha|first2=Aruna|date=13 July 2017|website=[[Wall Street Journal]]|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=11 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/7/14/15975140/alphabay-dark-web-drug-marketplace-police-shutdown-silk-road|title=Dark Web drug marketplace AlphaBay was shut down by law enforcement|last=Statt|first=Nick|date=14 July 2017|website=The Verge|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=11 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/story/alphabay-hansa-takedown-dark-web-trap/|title=Global Police Spring a Trap on Thousands of Dark Web Users|last=Greenberg|first=Andy|date=20 July 2017|website=WIRED|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=3 March 2018}}</ref> Many other [[darknet market]]s were also shutdown.<ref>{{cite news|title=Massive blow to criminal Dark Web activities after globally coordinated operation|url=https://www.europol.europa.eu/newsroom/news/massive-blow-to-criminal-dark-web-activities-after-globally-coordinated-operation|accessdate=20 July 2017|date=20 July 2017}}</ref>
